nge</guid></item><item><title>NF1 功能丧失作为胰腺导管腺癌的替代起始事件</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nf1-loss-of-function-as-an-alternative-initiating-event-in-pancreatic-ductal-adenocarcinoma</link><description>（细胞报告&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nf1-loss-of-function-as-an-alternative-initiating-event-in-pancreatic-ductal-adenocarcinoma.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 11:29:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nf1-loss-of-function-as-an-alternative-initiating-event-in-pancreatic-ductal-adenocarcinoma</guid></item><item><title>细胞死亡的“美丽”戒指！</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cell-deaths-beautiful-rings</link><description>在过去的几十年里，研究人员已经确定了植物中启动细胞自毁序列的基因和蛋白质。在此期间，他们还在哺乳动物中发现了这种“抵抗组”的共同元素。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cell-deaths-beautiful-rings2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 11:14:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cell-deaths-beautiful-rings</guid></item><item><title>MoS2/MoSe2 异质结构中的热电效应：实验证据和理论方面</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/thermoelectric-effect-in-mos2-mose2-heterostructures-experimental-evidence-and-theoretical-aspects</link><description>放射性同位素热电发电机和热回收系统等应用的高效能量收集需要具有卓越性能的新型热电材料。这项工作展示了热电能力&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/thermoelectric-effect-in-mos2-mose2-heterostructures-experimental-evidence-and-theoretical-aspects2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 10:59:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/thermoelectric-effect-in-mos2-mose2-heterostructures-experimental-evidence-and-theoretical-aspects</guid></item><item><title>出血之外：动脉瘤性蛛网膜下腔出血后的并发症。病理生理学、临床意义和管理策略：综述</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/beyond-the-bleed-complications-after-aneurysmal-subarachnoid-hemorrhage-pathophysiology-clinical-implications-and-management-strategies-a-review</link><description>动脉瘤性蛛网膜下腔出血是一种危重病症，病死率很高，并对幸存者产生持久影响。动脉瘤破裂直接导致的急性事件，如急性缺血、颅内压升高、脑水肿、癫痫发作和脑积水，会导致早期脑损伤。延迟的级联过程，包括显着的全身炎症反应，可能导致继发性脑损伤和延迟性脑缺血，这通常会进一步损害恢复。早期和继发性脑损伤之间的相互作用会出现全身并发症，包括心肺功能障碍、发烧和电解质失衡，并对临床病程提出挑战。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/beyond-the-bleed-complications-after-aneurysmal-subarachnoid-hemorrhage-pathophysiology-clinical-implications-and-management-strategies-a-review.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 10:44:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/beyond-the-bleed-complications-after-aneurysmal-subarachnoid-hemorrhage-pathophysiology-clinical-implications-and-management-strategies-a-review</guid></item><item><title>实践大型语言模型</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/hands-on-large-language-models</link><description>O&amp;#39;Reilly 书籍的官方代码存储库 — “Hands-On Large Language Models” — HandsOnLLM/Hands-On-Large-Language-Models&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/hands-on-large-language-models2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 10:29:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/hands-on-large-language-models</guid></item><item><title>长寿的遗传学：研究挑战数十年的衰老研究</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-genetics-of-living-longer-study-challenges-decades-of-aging-research</link><description>是什么决定了人们的寿命，以及他们的寿命有多少受到遗传的影响？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-genetics-of-living-longer-study-challenges-decades-of-aging-research.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 10:14:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-genetics-of-living-longer-study-challenges-decades-of-aging-research</guid></item></channel></rss>